name: Not Taco Bell Crunchy Taco
description: Our crunchy taco shells, introduced into the world by our founder in 1962, are cooked fresh daily with love and filled with only the freshest ingredients. Including seasoned beef, shredded cheese and lettuce.

name: Not McDonalds Big Mac
description: It starts with two 100% beef patties. Then comes the delicious combination of crisp iceberg lettuce, melting signature cheese, onions and pickles, between a toasted sesame seed bun. And don't forget the McDonald's special sauce!
ingrediants: [Beef Pattie, Lettuce, Cheese, Onions, Pickles, Sesame Seed Bun, Secret Sauce]

name: Not KFC Original Recipe Chicken
description: World-famous, mouth-watering Original Recipe chicken with 11 secret herbs and spices. Made with freshly prepared chicken pieces and cooked in-store.

name: Not Dominos Pepperoni Pizza
description: A classic. Slices of crispy pepperoni & creamy mozzarella
ingrediants: [Ham, Italian Sausage, Beef, and Mozzarella Cheese]

name: Not Krispy Kreme Original Glazed Doughnuts
description: When people talk about a doughnut, they're usually referring to our signature treat: the Original Glazed doughnut. Made from a recipe dating back to the 1930s, our Original Glazed doughnuts have helped set us apart. And if you haven't had an Original Glazed HOT off-the-line, you need to try one!

name: Not Hungry Jacks Big Whopper
description: Flame-grilled beef that gives you an irresistible, smoky BBQ flavour. Loaded with crisp fresh lettuce, ripe tomatoes, onion, pickles, mayo and tomato sauce on a toasted sesame seed bun. A legend for over 40 years.

name: Not McDonalds Quarter Pounder with Cheese
description: It's mighty simple, but it works. Take a whole quarter pound* of 100% beef, then complete the tasty picture with cheese, onions, tangy mustard and pickles. Bet your mouth is watering right now.

name: Not Starbucks Pumpkin Spice Latte
description: Our signature espresso and steamed milk with the celebrated flavor combination of pumpkin, cinnamon, nutmeg and clove. Enjoy it topped with whipped cream and real pumpkin-pie spices.
